def LoG(x, y, sigma=1):
    normal = 1 / (2.0 * torch.pi * sigma**2)
    return  ((x**2 + y**2 - (2.0*sigma**2)) / sigma**4) * \
        torch.exp(-(x**2+y**2) / (2.0*sigma**2)) / normal

def LoG_detection(img, sigma = 1):
    img0 = img[:,:,0].unsqueeze(0).unsqueeze(0)
    H,W = img[:,:,0].shape

    # three sigma rule
    n = sigma*3
    kernel_size = 2*n+1
    range_ = torch.arange(-n, n+1)
    xx = range_
    yy = range_

    XX, YY = torch.meshgrid(xx, yy)
    
    LoG_kernel = LoG(XX,YY,sigma)
    
    # convolution (filtering)
    conv = nn.Conv2d(1, 1, kernel_size = kernel_size, stride = 1, padding = (kernel_size-1)//2) #pad = (kernel_size-1)/2
    conv.weight = nn.Parameter(LoG_kernel.unsqueeze(0).unsqueeze(0))
    res = conv(Variable(img0)).data.reshape(H,W)
    
    # zero-crossing
    new_img = torch.zeros((H,W))
    for i in range(res.shape[0]-(kernel_size-1)):
        for j in range(res.shape[1]-(kernel_size-1)):
            if res[i][j] == 0:
                if (res[i][j-1] < 0 and res[i][j+1] > 0) or (res[i][j-1] < 0 and res[i][j+1] < 0) or (res[i-1][j] < 0 and res[i+1][j] > 0) or (res[i-1][j] > 0 and res[i+1][j] < 0):
                    new_img[i][j] = 255
            if res[i][j] < 0:
                if (res[i][j-1] > 0) or (res[i][j+1] > 0) or (res[i-1][j] > 0) or (res[i+1][j] > 0):
                    new_img[i][j] = 255
    
    return new_img.unsqueeze(0)
